cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CV 

The paper combines natural language processing (NLP) algorithms with supervised machine learning (ML) algorithms to improve classification performance. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). However, given the emphasis on semantic information and the use of NLP algorithms, cs.CL is the most likely sub-category. The other sub-categories are also relevant because they involve machine learning and classification tasks, but they are less likely because they do not explicitly mention NLP or semantic information.
